Physalis infinemundi
sp. nov. represents a derived lineage of Solanaceae in Gondwanan South America at 52.2 Ma, pushing back considerably the evolutionary timing of the family. Compared with recent molecular divergence estimates (
10
), these fossils are considerably older than the ~30 Ma crown for the entire Solanaceae family as well as the ~11 Ma divergence of Physalinae . A second recent study similarly placed the Physalinae divergence at only ~9 Ma (
13
).
